Yo gang! After three long years we are proud to announce the release of a collaborative project thats been in the works between a collective of humans all around the world. ‚õΩÔ∏è

The project is a experimental piece produced by Hypho & Abstrakt Sonance and the vocals recorded by Megumi Hope aka Dub Princess. We came together during lockdown with a passion to create something beautiful which would stand the rest of time üíú It was a very exciting time in the studio working alongside these two over the internet, each of us stuck at home like the rest of the world. We wanted to make use of our time and create something beautiful to help process the suffering we were all collectively feeling. 

Pre orders for the record are available now via the DDD Bandcamp. A LTD run of T shirts are also available in the short linküëï 

The first single of the release will be out the 26th October which is titled ‚ÄòMy Mind‚Äô üß†  big love to BBC introducing for premiering this track on BBC radio Cumbria on Sunday! üôè

The full release will be available the 6th November üóìÔ∏è

Luke Gray created a stunning painting for the EP cover. It represents us all coming together as one and being in touch with our feminine. Our desire to acknowledge the challenges anxiety brings and how we use music as a tool to heal our traumas, trials and tribulations. We want to live in a world that communicates and comes together in love and peace ‚òÆÔ∏è @lukegrayart üñºÔ∏è 

@dubprincessmusic 
@abstraktsonance 
@deepdarkand_dangerous

We would like to support humanity as a whole and those currently in conflict and suffering, have all of our support no sides taken. We are all one. This song is to express our passion for the peace, love and unity of humanity and to remind us to come together because we will rise together.

